All of our handlers currently get a "proxy" / "tchannel" / "channel" argument that is conceptually confusing and error-prone. It's purpose is to tie together zipkin tracing information, but it's too easy for users to not use it. It *should* be a totally reasonable pattern to write some wrappers around service calls that use the global tchannel, versus needing to plumb this proxy object everywhere.

Let's make the proxy argument optional. For backwards compatibility maybe we could infer its presence from the handler's signature?

```
@app.register(...)
def foo(request, response, proxy):
    pass

@app.register(...)
def foo(request, response):
    pass
``` 

In the latter case, we should hook up a [StackContext](http://tornado.readthedocs.org/en/latest/_modules/tornado/stack_context.html) to the handler that tracks the current trace id / span id such that subsequent tchannel calls automatically send that information downstream.

